Hi [~wilfreds] - thanks for the patch, it looks good.

One minor suggestion: in NMLeveldbStateStoreService I would keep the isHealthy boolean private, and expose only a @VisibleForTesting getter for testing. 

Nit: (I have no strong feelings about this) the assertions in {{TestNMLeveldbStateStoreService.testStateStoreNodeHealth()}} may be more readable this way:
{code}
    try {
      // chosen a simple method could be any of the "void" methods
      ContainerId containerId = ContainerId.newContainerId(appAttemptId, 1);
      stateStore.storeContainerKilled(containerId);
      Assert.fail("Expected exception not thrown");
    } catch (IOException ioErr) {
      // Cause should be wrapped DBException
      assertTrue(ioErr.getCause() instanceof DBException);
      // check the store is marked unhealthy
      assertFalse("Statestore should have been unhealthy",
          stateStore.isHealthy);
    } finally {
      // restore the working DB
      stateStore.setDB(keepDB);
    }
{code}
